description.3: A story ten years in the future! After the shocking events of last issue, ten years have passed, and the world has still not fully recovered- least of all the Hulk!
description.6: Captain America's shield is shattered and trashed... What's the Cap to do without his most trusted sidekick?!
description.7: Deathbird and Bishop have crash-landed on a planet full of murderous aliens.
description.8: Hydra and the Hand face Wolverine's wrath following his ""marriage"" to one of Madripoor's top crime lords.
description.12: METAMORPHOSIS! Plant-Man uses Synch's ability to synchronize with other mutants to cause chaos in the city.
description.13: Cable faces off against the Pharaoh, Rama-Tut!
description.14: It all comes down to the Human Torch! Johnny makes a shocking discovery at the Starlight Citadel about Franklin! Is he willing to sacrifice his entire reality to save his nephew?! Plus, a backup story featuring the mysterious Inhumans!
description.15: Things keep getting worse for Roberto Da Costa, but money troubles and having an evil doppelganger are nothing compared to having said doppelganger take over his body!
description.22: Grand Admiral Thrawn sets his trap for the New Republic as they arrive through hyperspace to the Bilbringi Shipyards. Meanwhile, Luke and Mara Jade confront Jedi Master C'baoth in his hidden prison chambers inside Mount Tantiss. C'baoth has a surprise waiting for Luke, and as Luke faces himself, the true battle of the Force begins.
description.23: Ulic is haunted by his decisions, but will his next decision be the worst of all?
description.24: When Imperial Intelligence chief Ysanne Isard discovers that acting-Emperor Pestage has made a deal with the Rebel Alliance, it appears that the Rebels' ticket to Imperial Center has been punched. But a Rebel operative witnesses Pestage's capture, and Rogue Squadron is assigned to go after him.
description.32: The unthinkable happens this issue! Someone closer to the Hulk than anyone else dies, and the life of both Hulk and Bruce Banner will never be the same.
description.35: The evil alien Skrull has caused mass panic nationwide! Will Captain America be able to solve the hysteria before it is too late?
description.36: In Alaska, the X-Men battle a strange swarm of crows. Does this signal the coming of the Crow God? Meanwhile in space, Bishop and Deathbird are on a collision course with a planet!
description.37: Wolverine gets married, and Sabretooth is right on cue to spoil yet another special day. See how (and why) Wolverine and Viper say ""I do!"" in their marriage of crime and convenience.
description.40: The Fantastic Four battle the villain group Technet before they can make off with Franklin!
description.44: The First Thor #1 issue ever!  To aid his fellow Avengers, Thor must do battle with the Destroyer!
description.49: THE BIG REVEAL! The Black Tarantula's motive for returning to New York is revealed as well as the Rose's true identity.
description.50: Cable isn't one to hold a grudge. Who are we kidding? Of course he is, and this time, Blockade is in his crosshairs.
description.52: Take a closer look at the various elements that make Star Wars'so special: the characters, ships, planets, and aliens. No fan of Star Wars'and'Star Wars: X-Wing Rogue Squadron'should be without this title!
description.53: Why is Natasha Romanoff, A.K.A. Black Widow, turning to Tony Stark for help? The Avengers may have gotten themselves in too deep- but with what?
description.56: Guri, the most wanted droid in the galaxy awakens from surgery. Doc and Thrumble stand by to see if the surgery successfully removed the bad memories of Black Sun. Meanwhile, our gang is on the way to collect Guri and bring her to trial. What they don't know is that Savan and her thugs are there to capture Guri for themselves.
description.61: Rogue Squadron faces off against the pirates of the Blazing Claw, but no sooner have they sent them packing than an Imperial Star Destroyer makes orbit! It's time for Baron Fel to show his true colors as the fate of Rogue Squadron hangs in the balance!
description.62: Collects Jabba the Hutt: The Gaar Suppoon Hit, Jabba the Hutt: The Hunger of Princess Nampi, Jabba the Hutt: The Dynasty Trap & Jabba the Hutt: Betrayal.  Before his death at the hands of Princess Leia, Jabba the Hutt was known throughout the galaxy as the vilest gangster of them all. In these gruesome tales of power and corruption, he is pitted against rival crime-lords. Jabba lives to negotiate, and the art of the deal is his only discipline.
description.63: We meet Hannibal King's first vampire progeny (and conversion), Tatjana Stiles. Was she his biggest mistake or his greatest triumph? You won't want to miss the next chapter in the life of the one and only Vampire Detective!
description.68: Rick Jones has been paralyzed, and the Hulk wants to help his dearest friend. The Jade Giant embarks on a recruitment drive to get the three smartest men on Earth to help - Reed Richards, Tony Stark, and Bruce Banner himself!
description.71: A Skrull starts posing as Captain America all while the nation is immersed in Capmania! This villain plans on using this to his advantage and wants to cause mass hysteria while Captain America is at his most vulnerable state!
description.72: Cyclops thinks it may be time to reassess Professor Xavier's dream and so he invites the X-Men to his new home in Alaska. But Scott has another motive for gathering his teammates: Jean Grey's recent interactions with the Phoenix Force may be spiraling out of control...
description.73: A ""Blood Wedding"" leads to a shocking revelation for Wolverine and the (former) ladies in his life. Viper, the wife of Wolverine?!
description.76: Terror strikes Pier Four! While Reed and Sue Richards are out on a date, a new enemy attacks their home with the intentions of kidnapping their son, Franklin! Meanwhile, Alyssa has a strange feeling that something's wrong with Reed...
description.77: Reignfire has returned but it’s not who you think it is!
description.81: SPIDER MAN AS "RICOCHET!" Spider-Man battles the Black Tarantula's goons portraying all of his new identities.
description.82: The master assassin Domino is finally back to get under Cable’s skin…and if she's lucky, she’ll be around for a long time! See the sparks fly between these two!
description.85: The Hornet, one of Spidey’s four new identities, goes out for his first crime-stopping stint! The Avengers cameo!
description.88: Elektra's back in New York City, but much has changed. A betrayal lies in wait for Marvel's deadliest assassin, sprung by someone very close to Elektra.
description.89: Black Widow's on back-up! Check out the fiery (and final), confrontation between Firebrand and Iron Man!
description.90: This is it! The final battle: the last of the'Royal Guards,'Kir Kanos'versus Carnor Jax, and only one walks away! Who wins? Who dies? And what is the fate of the'Rebels?
description.91: Now that Guri has found Doc, and the de-droiding procedure has been started, the search is on for Guri. Will Spinda Caveel, the Pikkel Sisters, Savan, or Han, Luke, and Leia be the first to find Guri and Doc? Will Doc be able to finish the Humanizing procedure on Guri before they are found? Just as we think things are going well, Luke gets a "feeling," and Leia discovers the truth behind Savan.
description.96: Wolverine fighting side-by-side with CAPTAIN AMERICA!
description.97: As Wedge and Princess Leia complete their negotiations with the interim Emperor, Tycho and Winter make their break from the pirate thugs of Leonia Tavira. But both teams working in separate parts of the galaxy on the same caper are about to find they have something else in common: trouble!
description.99: On the path to regaining her soul, Nina, with Elektra's assistance, tries to gain entry to the Chaste stronghold. Elektra learns a shocking secret about her mother.

0.text: The Black Knight has a modern-day  dragon crusade against Wall Street hotshot Malcolm Drake!

1.text: FLYING BLIND PART 3 ‘Laurent’ has a Parisian smack down with several of Kingpin’s thugs. Foggy and S.H.I.E.L.D. begin to put the pieces together on Murdock. The Man Without Fear is in serious trouble- will DD snap out of his amnesia before it’s too late?

2.text: Nightcrawler's search for Professor X uncovers the Mimic instead. Can Excalibur stop a mutant who can copy all of their powers?

9.text: Could this be Psylocke's last stand? Behold the psychic ninja and the Shadow King in hand-to-hand combat on the Astral Plane!

10.text: The Goblin, after learning about the missing Osborn journal, makes a deal with Kingsley to find its whereabouts.

11.text: Live Kree or Die tie-in! Quicksilver joins an elite team of Avengers to thwart a Kree attack from Earth’s moon. The Kree have targeted an Omni-wave projector at our planet, set to decimate at any moment. With time of the essence, Quicksilver may be the speedy recovery this mission needs!

13.text: Cable faces off against the Pharaoh, Rama-Tut!

18.text: Thor has fallen! While the Avengers continue their battle against the Destroyer, Thor must contend with Hela, dark mistress of the underworld!

19.text: Namor and the Hulk team up against a threat from beneath the waves!

20.text: Through the perspective of Pepper Potts, we learn of Tony Stark’s origin: through his rise as CEO of Stark Industries, to his first turn as Iron Man.

21.text: The Invaders…reassembled! Marvel’s World War II-age heroes reunite to dissemble both the Axis…and Hydra!

29.text: S.H.I.E.L.D. is determined to make the Thunderbolts pay for their betrayal, but will Nick Fury’s forces turn up empty? Citizen V continues a path of devastation leaving enemy and ally in danger!

30.text: FLYING BLIND PART 2 Stateside, Foggy begins to search for the missing Matt Murdock. In France, undercover agent Laurent Levasseur struggles to understand his affinity for tights and crime fighting. Will Levasseur realize that he and Daredevil are one in the same?

38.text: Storm and the X-Men travel to Kenya to aid Ainet, Ororo’s former mentor.

39.text: Our favorite Spider-Man villain is back to his old antics! The Green Goblin breaks Kingsley out of prison after learning about the existence of an Osborn journal.

44.text: To aid his fellow Avengers, Thor must do battle with the Destroyer!

45.text: The rise of Baron Wolfgang von Strucker! Due to an act of time travel, the mad Nazi travels back to the age of World War II equipped with precious intel from the modern age that will guarantee a win by the Third Reich. But then the Invaders swoop in…

46.text: IN THE FOLD PART 1 Iron Fist reflects on his past while embarking on a trip to San Francisco. What depths of madness led to Daniel Rand’s awakening in K’un-Lun? Iron Fist finds himself in an airport skirmish after a mysterious assailant makes a bold and devastating move!

47.text: The Heroes for Hire use unconventional ways to save Hammond and Danny Rand. Scott travels into Hammond’s body where he finds the Controller’s device in his brain!

48.text: Hated and feared by a world they are sworn to protect, the X-Men face off against some of their most unforgettable foes' including Magneto and the Hellfire Club.

50.text: Cable isn't one to hold a grudge. Who are we kidding? Of course he is, and this time, Blockade is in his crosshairs.

51.text: Attack of the Acolytes! Quicksilver ignites a feud with Exodus, following an attack from his terroristic band of mutants. In battle, Lord Anon crosses a line he has never crossed before.

54.text: The embodiment of Death helps Deadpool remember his troubled past in the Weapon X facility.

57.text: It's the Avengers versus the Squadron Supreme! Never have the Earth's Mightiest Heroes battled a team so like themselves and yet, so different! Who is behind this ferocious battle between the two superteams?

60.text: No sooner does the team return to Earth, than they are hunted by the hordes of S.H.I.E.L.D.! Will the Thunderbolts be able to escape a vigilant taskforce much stronger than their own? Baron Zemo and Techno return!

64.text: Things get wild when Alpha Flight and the X-Men unleash their combined force against Baron von Strucker and his Hydra agents!

65.text: Quicksilver and the Knights of Wundagore discover something amiss with the High Evolutionary. What bizarre transformation has overcome Pietro’s most feared villain? Lord Anon stages a rescue for his fellow teammates.

66.text: FLYING BLIND PART 1 Daredevil is all alone in a foreign country. With no recollection of his life as Matt Murdock, the Man Without Fear has no support and no ties to his true identity. An existential crisis at its finest. Plus, who is Laurent Levasseur?

67.text: Three personalities of Legion hover on the verge of death. Can Excalibur solve this reality-warping and death-defying problem?

69.text: Spider-Man is "stuck in the middle” as his battle with the Trapster continues.

74.text: Wolverine learns about Maggott's strange upbringing, as well as how Magneto initially helped him to control his mutant powers.

75.text: Introducing the Spectacular Prodigy! Peter's new hero identity gets its trial by fire when the Jack-O-Lantern strikes!

78.text: When Nightcrawler's adopted mother is captured by the demon Belasco, Kurt will have to journey to Limbo to rescue her. And the only way to rescue her will be a shocking choice!

82.text: The master assassin Domino is finally back to get under Cable’s skin…and if she's lucky, she’ll be around for a long time! See the sparks fly between these two!

83.text: Battle of the mechanized men! Machine Man and Bastion duke it out in a gritty battle featuring Cable! Plus, Bastion’s full origin revealed.

84.text: Ka-Zar must harness the powers within the Savage Land (and his fellow compatriots) to defeat the High Evolutionary! Plus, the fate of Shanna!

86.text: Journey back to Marvel’s Golden Age with this special adventure starring Namor, Captain America, and Jim Hammond, the first Human Torch! Hydra and their goons don’t stand a chance!

87.text: The Heroes for Hire battle against their evil counterparts, Strike Force One, lead by The Master and Luke Cage!

88.text: Elektra's back in New York City, but much has changed. A betrayal lies in wait for Marvel's deadliest assassin, sprung by someone very close to Elektra.

93.text: The Avengers have emerged victorious from their last battle. Now it is time to form the new roster for the superhero team. Who will be chosen? Who will be left out?

96.text: Wolverine fighting side-by-side with CAPTAIN AMERICA!

98.text: Luke Cage plots an escape heist after the Heroes are kidnapped by Silver Sable and the Wild Pack. And they don’t call her pack “wild” for nothing. This is Luke Cage at his best!

99.text: On the path to regaining her soul, Nina, with Elektra's assistance, tries to gain entry to the Chaste stronghold. Elektra learns a shocking secret about her mother.
